,Recommended,227780,9983413,"Posted: 30 April, 2014",all,ThatDarnOwl,"SSR is an enhanced re-release of both encounters of Serious Sam 1. This was done for numerous reasons, one of the biggest being how SS1's multiplayer servers were taken down by Gamespy.SSR features a very large amount of levels, workshop support, 64 bit support and numerous other things. I could go into depth about what made Serious Sam great but fundamentally, you have to play it to see why.The strengths of Serious Sam could easily be compared to games like Doom or Quake. In that it is the level design and enemy placement that makes it unique and stand out. Every enemy in Serious Sam by themselves are♥♥♥♥♥♥easy to kill. However when the level throws hundreds of them at you, you start noticing just how hard the game is. It is a very rewarding game, and truly one of the best examples of a ""classic FPS""Of course if you don't wanna play alone there's 16 player coop, and deathmatch. With the many varied levels of the first and second encounters, and the hundreds more due to arrive on the workshop. Serious Sam Revolution is one of the best ways to spend 10$ on Steam.Or you could just buy SS Gold, you get it for free there. Jus' saying..."
