,Recommended,227780,9983813,"Posted: 30 April, 2014",all,Dildaddy™,"Ahhh, Serious Sam...a budget-priced, nostalgic bundle of fun to many. And well...that counts to me; somewhat. I mean, the first SS game I played was Next Encounter for the PS2, and it was a crazy good time! But what about the classic games? Despite their large fan community and mod support; something didn't feel quite...""modern"" with the games.Enter Serious Sam Revolution, a fan-made version of the classic Serious Sam titles made by some of the most well-known and diehard SS fans from around the globe. While it's in Early Access at the moment, the full version of Revolution will include a new campaign, new gamemodes and much more. And how did this grab my attention? Well, because it was fuggin free! Well, it is free but you gotta own both classic titles. How does this fare? Well...The gameplay of SS Revolution are like any other Serious Sam game: shoot enemies, get new weapons, shoot more enemies, kill a boss, you get the idea. Sometimes you can get a friend or family member to help out with slaughtering mass hordes of enemies with a minigun. Graphics? Same as the classic games. Old, but impressive for the time....and this time with OpenGL.As for Revolution itself, the new Steam-based features are pretty cool; with leaderboard support, achievements and Workshop, and more streamlined multiplayer. Of course, seeing how this is a Early Access game, I noticed a rather odd bug where the Workshop items wouldn't load, but it might be because I'm not loading them right or it really is a bug, but eh. <.<Still, if ya want a dose of nostalgia get this game! I sincerly can't wait for the full release and maybe hear John J.♥♥♥♥♥♥s secksy voice in the new campaign mode, lol."
