,Recommended,227780,29959854,Posted: 16 February,all,WESCO,"This is essentially the ZDoom of Serious Sam, though it isn't feature complete yet. The original First and Second encounter have issues running on modern hardware, and have terrible mouse control. This version fixes most of these inconveniences.However it is buggy from time to time. Playing co-op with a friend, Aludran Reptiloids would occasionally slide off their sniping platforms and fall off the map. Considering typically all enemies must be eliminated to continue, this can be a problem. Sometimes getting grenades or cannonballs to fall off the maps as well can get the kill, but gameplay bugs like this are not something I ever encountered in the original Serious Sam or the HD remakes.Hopefully all these issues will be ironed out when this is finished eventually, as the co-op options and gameplay are generally superior in this version when compared to the HD remakes. Despite its flaws, this is the definitive version of Serious Sam."
