,Recommended,227780,10002255,"Posted: 2 May, 2014",all,Stoat,"Having kept up with this game through the Seriouszone forums, I was quite happy when it finally appeared in my library. And apart from some funny business in the beginning with saving/loading (an issue that has since been fixed) it has done well to meet my expectations.What this game is exactly is simple, it's a combination of the original First and Second Encounters optimized for modern hardware. The developers have been kind enough to go beyond that as well, they've updated the editor, integrated the whole game with Steam, added a Survival mode, and revamped the networking software. And that's all in the Early Access version. The final version promises a new single-player campaign, added gamemodes, weapons, and modding capabilities, trading-cards, and some demonstration maps for the new features.Aside from all that however the game is authentic and almost-unaltered Serious Sam Classic, that means crazy gravity, harpies that don't auto-gib, insane ammo-consuming miniguns, slower grenade launcher firerate, and non-xbox style models.  They did however go for one unified sound with the lasergun across both Encounters, and that is good, makes FE less headache inducing. I also enjoy being able to use the Second Encounter HUD for the game, as it's always been my favorite in the whole series.I don't know if the current price (9.99) will go up after the final version is released, but for now it remains one of the best deals on the SS Classics you can get, and it's already cheaper than buying both Encounters on GOG. It's updated often to take care of those harmful bugs and the devs seem quite dedicated to their craft.Overall I'd mainly recommend Revolution to those who want to experience the original Serious Sam games on current hardware, without needing the processing power required for the HD versions. If you're like me and also appreciate the smaller, less signifcant details, then you'll probably enjoy being able to go from The Great Pyramid to Sierra De Chiapes without starting a new game, as well as the general extra polish SS Classic has over the HD versions."
